2%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20mother%20of%2010.%20My%20life%20is%20like%20hosting%20a%20birthday%20party%20every%20day%20%E2%80%94%26nbsp%3Bhere%20are%20my%20best%20budgeting%20tips%20for%20food%20and%20essentials.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jane%20Brosseau%2C%20a%20mother%20of%2010%20with%20her%20family%20in%20a%20garden.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65082906f05aa00019be03a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJane%20Brosseau%20has%2010%20children%20between%20the%20ages%20of%204%20and%2019.%3Cp%3EJane%20Brosseau%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJane%20Brosseau%20and%20her%20husband%20have%2010%20children%20between%20the%20ages%20of%204%20and%2019.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20having%20a%20big%20family%20is%20like%20a%20birthday%20party%20where%20the%20guests%20never%20leave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrosseau%20shares%20her%20best%20budgeting%20tips%20for%20grocery%20shopping%20and%20events%20such%20as%20Christmas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jane%20Brosseau%2C%20a%20mom%20of%2010%20and%20blogger%20at%2010%20Busy%20Bees%20in%20southern%20Washington.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20an%20only%20child%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20think%20I'd%20have%2010%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20oldest%20is%2019%2C%20and%20our%20youngest%20just%20turned%204.%20We%20have%20every%20age%20in%20between%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20any%20twins.%20Our%20oldest%20is%20starting%20her%20sophomore%20year%20of%20college%2C%20so%20we%20have%20nine%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20with%20a%20blog%2C%20but%20I'm%20mostly%20active%20on%20social%20media.%20It's%20been%20a%20great%20outlet%20and%20connector%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20met%20large-family%20moms%20across%20the%20country%20via%20social%20media.%20It's%20been%20fun%20to%20trade%20tips%20and%20tricks%2C%20and%20my%20online%20community%20has%20become%20my%20real-life%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20works%20full%20time%20in%20sales%20and%20travels%20weekly%20for%20work%2C%20so%20it%20wasn't%20economical%20for%20me%20to%20work%20in%20tandem%20with%20childcare.%20I%20earn%20some%20income%20from%20affiliate%20partnerships%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20consistent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20always%20compare%20large%20families%20to%20reality-TV%20stereotypes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20hear%20we're%20a%20large%20family%2C%20they%20immediately%20compare%20us%20to%20the%20Duggars%2C%20but%20that's%20a%20negative%20stereotype%20of%20big%20families.%20I%20think%20large%20families%20are%20still%20regular%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoms%20of%20large%20families%20are%20often%20seen%20as%20supermoms%2C%20but%20we%20have%20hard%20days%20just%20like%20everybody%20else%20and%20need%20help%20sometimes.%20When%20I%20share%20that%20on%20social%20media%2C%20I%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20pushback%2C%20with%20people%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20asked%20for%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%20that%20we%20had%20another%20baby%2C%20we%20lost%20friends.%20After%20our%20fifth%20child%2C%20even%20family%20and%20close%20friends%20would%20make%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20a%20big%20family%20is%20like%20hosting%20a%20birthday%20party%20every%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20large%20family%20is%20like%20hosting%20a%20birthday%20party%20every%20day.%20The%20amount%20of%20work%2C%20effort%2C%20food%2C%20and%20logistics%20that%20goes%20into%20hosting%20a%20birthday%20party%20at%20your%20house%20is%20what%20I%20do%20every%20day%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20guests%20never%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20has%20taken%20its%20toll%20on%20us.%20It's%20been%20stressful.%20The%20increase%20in%20the%20costs%20of%20gas%20and%20groceries%20has%20taken%20away%20any%20extra%20we%20had%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20not%20wealthy.%20We%20stick%20to%20a%20strict%20budget%20and%20meet%20all%20our%20kids'%20needs.%20Big%20families%20are%20master%20recyclers%20and%20waste%20little.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20drowning%20financially%20right%20now.%20We%20might%20not%20be%20in%20the%20same%20boat%2C%20but%20we're%20in%20the%20same%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20I%20budget%20groceries%20for%20a%20big%20family%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20time%20or%20energy%20to%20visit%20multiple%20grocery%20stores%20to%20find%20the%20best%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20leave%20the%20house%2C%20I%20always%20have%20a%20flexible%20meal%20plan.%20I%20plan%20meals%20where%20if%20one%20ingredient%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20very%20expensive%2C%20I%20can%20swap%20it%20out.%20Or%20if%20something's%20on%20sale%2C%20I%20can%20swap%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20check%20my%20pantry%2C%20freezer%2C%20and%20fridge%20before%20I%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%20so%20I%20don't%20buy%20duplicates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20use%20rewards%20cards%20at%20our%20local%20grocery%20stores%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20Fred%20Meyer%2C%20Walmart%2C%20or%20Costco.%20I%20log%20into%20the%20store's%20app%20before%20I%20get%20there%20to%20use%20digital%20coupons%20and%20reward%20programs%20as%20I%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20I%20used%20to%20buy%20that%20I%20don't%20get%20anymore.%20Treats%20are%20now%20a%20luxury%20%E2%80%94%20even%20from%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20found%20that%20chicken%20drumsticks%20are%20a%20great%20deal%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20get%20a%20gigantic%20family%20pack%20for%20%245%20or%20%247.%20We%20also%20are%20buying%20more%20frozen%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20because%20fresh%20produce%20is%20so%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20cutting%20out%20the%20treats%20and%20buying%20generic%20brands%2C%20we%20still%20spend%20%24600%20a%20week%20on%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20budget%20for%20Christmas%20and%20birthdays%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20expensive%20times%20of%20the%20year%20such%20as%20Christmas%2C%20we%20stick%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCmMnRpPp4UJ%2F%3Figshid%3DMzRlODBiNWFlZA%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebudget%20to%20stay%20on%20track%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20budgeted%20%24250%20a%20child%20for%20gifts%20and%20stocking%20stuffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20budget%20%24200%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bfamily%26quot%3B%20gift%2C%20%24100%20for%20gifts%20for%20my%20husband%20and%20me%2C%20%2450%20for%20grandparents'%20gifts%2C%20and%20%24100%20for%20teacher%20and%20bus-driver%20gifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%2C%20but%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20we%20use%20cash-back%20and%20reward%20programs%2C%20shop%20on%20Facebook%20Marketplace%20or%20in%20secondhand%20stores%2C%20and%20regift%20gently%20used%20or%20new%20toys%20friends%20have%20given%20to%20our%20children.%20Sometimes%20we%20also%20have%20family%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20back-to-school%20season%2C%20we%20shop%20sales%20for%20supplies%20and%20use%20supplies%20we%20have%20from%20previous%20years.%20We%20also%20don't%20buy%20our%20kids%20first-day-of-school%20outfits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20use%20the%20cash-back%20app%20Rakuten%20for%20both%20back-to-school%20and%20Christmas%20shopping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20find%20affordable%20housing%20for%20big%20families%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20has%20been%20a%20huge%20stressor.%20In%20August%202020%2C%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20we%20moved%20from%20Northern%20Virginia%20outside%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20to%20southern%20Washington%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20sold%20our%20house%20in%20Virginia%20and%20were%20renting%20to%20own%20when%20the%20market%20blew%20up.%20We've%20been%20renting%20for%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20and%20we've%20had%20to%20move%20yearly%20because%20of%20rising%20rents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20owned%20our%20home%20in%20Virginia%20for%2016%20years%2C%20so%20we%20hadn't%20thought%20about%20the%20bias%20we%20would%20face%20as%20a%20large%20family%20trying%20to%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20I%20was%20looking%20around%20the%20area%20for%20parks%20where%20we%20could%20do%20short-term%20stays%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FCuzefrXMfgX%2F%3Figshid%3DMzRlODBiNWFlZA%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enobody%20would%20rent%20to%20us%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20came%20out%20West%20naive%20%E2%80%94%20we%20should%20have%20done%20more%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20tough%20journey%2C%20so%20we're%20heading%20back%20to%20the%20East%20Coast%20after%20this%20year%20because%20we%20just%20can't%20afford%20the%20high%20housing%20costs%2C%20the%20gas%2C%20and%20the%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20family%20of%2012%20isn't%20easy%2C%20but%20it's%20worth%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20older%20kids%20probably%20wish%20we%20didn't%20have%20as%20many%20kids%2C%20but%20it's%20all%20the%20younger%20ones%20have%20ever%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20them%20about%20my%20childhood%2C%20when%20it%20was%20just%20me%20and%20my%20parents%2C%20so%20books%20were%20my%20friends.%20They%20always%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BMom%2C%20that's%20so%20sad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20our%20share%20of%20sibling%20squabbles%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20amazing%20thing%2C%20especially%20because%20I'm%20an%20only%20child%2C%20to%20see%20their%20bond.%20I%20don't%20know%20many%20people%20who%20can%20say%20that%20they%20have%20nine%20other%20people%20who%20have%20their%20backs%20no%20mat