le's%20AI%20division%20DeepMind%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20there%20are%20certain%20capabilities%20we%20should%20rule%20out%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20artificial%20intelligence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2023%2F09%2F15%2F1079624%2Fdeepmind-inflection-generative-ai-whats-next-mustafa-suleyman%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20MIT%20Technology%20Review%2C%20Suleyman%20suggested%20that%20we%20should%20rule%20out%20%26quot%3Brecursive%20self-improvement%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20the%20ability%20for%20AI%20to%20make%20itself%20better%20over%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20let%20your%20little%20AI%20go%20off%20and%20update%20its%20own%20code%20without%20you%20having%20oversight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20MIT%20Technology%20Review.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20that%20should%20even%20be%20a%20licensed%20activity%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20just%20like%20for%20handling%20anthrax%20or%20nuclear%20materials.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20there's%20been%20a%20considerable%20focus%20on%20AI%20regulation%20at%20an%20institutional%20level%20%E2%80%94%20just%20last%20week%2C%20tech%20execs%20including%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20and%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-regulate-ai-tech-washington-musk-zuckerberg-gates-altman-2023-9%5C%22%3Egathered%20in%20Washington%20for%20a%20closed-door%20forum%20on%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Suleyman%20added%20that%20it's%20important%20for%20people%20to%20set%20limits%20around%20how%20their%20personal%20data%20is%20used%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEssentially%2C%20it's%20about%20setting%20boundaries%2C%20limits%20that%20an%20AI%20can't%20cross%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20MIT%20Technology%20Review%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20ensuring%20that%20those%20boundaries%20create%20provable%