cal%20polarisation%2C%20refugee%20crises%2C%20shifting%20global%20power%20dynamics%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20China%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20BRICS%2B%20powers%20and%20new%20regional%20configurations.%20The%20US%20and%20its%20Western%20partners%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20only%20game%20in%20town.%20Along%20with%20shifts%20in%20power%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20redistribution%20of%20self-confidence%20and%20rekindling%20of%20postcolonial%20resentment%20as%20re-emerging%20powers%20demand%20status%20and%20position%20in%20world%20affairs.%20In%20waging%20an%20illegal%20war%20in%20Iraq%2C%20the%20United%20States%20ended%20up%20losing%20face%2C%20losing%20ground%20geopolitically%20to%20its%20arch-enemy%2C%20Iran%2C%20alienating%20Turkey%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20quiet%20rise%20of%20China%20and%20likely%20encouraging%20Russia%20to%20invade%20Ukraine%20two%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20very%20different%2C%20transitional%20and%20volatile%20world%2C%20the%20US%20no%20longer%20occupies%20a%20credible%20position%20of%20moral%20authority%2C%20nor%20a%20virtually%20unassailable%20position%20in%20the%20Liberal%20International%20Order%2C%20being%20more%20wedded%20to%20America%20Firstism%20than%20multilateralism.%20The%20COVID-19%20global%20pandemic%20demonstrated%20through%20%E2%80%9Cvaccine%20nationalism%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20hoarding%20by%20the%20powerful%20West%20of%20the%20bulk%20of%20life-saving%20medical%20supplies%20and%20patents%20%E2%80%93%20who%20runs%20the%20world%20and%20for%20whom.%20And%20the%20illegal%20freezing%20and%20seizure%20of%20Russian%20financial%20assets%20in%20the%20West%20%E2%80%93%20totalling%20around%20%24300%20billion%20%E2%80%93%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20sent%20a%20signal%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98rest%E2%80%99%3A%20Look%20after%20your%20own%20interests%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20western%20superpower%20protects%20and%20extends%20its%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIraq%20was%20not%20a%20limited%20war%2C%20a%20small%20war%20in%20a%20far-off%20place%20with%20no%20impact%20on%20the%20region%20or%20world%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20US%20body%20politic.%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20fundamental%20inflection%20point%20of%20US%20global%20primacy%20and%20credibility%20%E2%80%93%20exposing%20certain%20basics%20of%20US%20imperial%20power%2C%20paranoia%20and%20hubris%2C%20administering%20a%20shock%20to%20the%20world%20that%20triggered%20what%20may%20be%20an%20irreversible%20power%20dynamic%20%E2%80%93%20the%20rise%20of%20new%20regional%20and%20global%20powers%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20most%20worryingly%20the%20redundancy%20of%20international%20law.%20Add%20in%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008%2C%20and%20the%20disasters%20in%20Libya%20and%20Syria%2C%20and%20we%20begin%20to%20appreciate%20the%20basic%20crises%20of%20legitimacy%20that%20lie%20at%20the%20core%20of%20global%20and%20US%20dynamics%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20did%20the%20war%20really%20take%20place%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Bush%20administration%2C%20war%20was%20inevitable%20because%20Iraq%20possessed%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction%20(WMDs)%2C%20was%20connected%20to%20Al%20Qaeda%20and%20terrorism%2C%20and%20posed%20a%20security%20threat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20%E2%80%98security%20school%E2%80%99%20of%20thought%20is%20supplemented%20with%20liberal%20variants%20which%20suggest%20that%20the%20Iraq%20threat%20was%20exaggerated%20or%20that%20a%20war%20would%20be%20counter-productive%20even%20if%20promoting%20democracy%20was%20in%20itself%20appropriate.%20Liberals%20also%20suggest%20the%20war%20was%20poorly-conceived%20and%20largely%20unplanned%2C%20riddled%20with%20errors%2C%20although%20motivated%20by%20good%20intentions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20variants%20of%20the%20security%20school%20compete%20principally%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98hegemonic%20school%E2%80%99%20which%20argues%20that%20the%20Bush%20elite%20used%20security%20and%20terrorism%20to%20justify%20the%20US%20goal%20of%20regional%20and%20global%20hegemony.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20dominant%20mainstream%20debate%2C%20while%20important%2C%20is%20ripe%20for%20challenge%20in%20different%20ways.%20We%20largely%20reject%20the%20security%20school%E2%80%99s%20arguments%2C%20but%20while%20we%20support%20the%20hegemonic%20explanation%20in%20broad%20terms%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20clear%20that%20neither%20school%20pays%20enough%20attention%20to%20the%20details%20of%20the%20Iraq%20war%20%E2%80%93%20from%20its%20conception%2C%20to%20decisions%20on%20the%20ground%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20war%E2%80%99s%20repercussions%20and%20legacies.%20For%20such%20a%20voluble%20proponent%20of%20democracy%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20on%20the%20global%20stage%2C%20America%E2%80%99s%20conceptions%20and%20conduct%20in%20Iraq%20offer%20a%20terrible%20lesson%20in%20imperial%20hubris%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-nearly-gave-us-pressure-join-iraq-war%5C%22%3EHow%20India%20Nearly%20Gave%20in%20to%20US%20Pressure%20to%20Enter%20the%20Iraqi%20Killing%20Zone%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20a%20mistake%20but%20an%20elite%20strategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FElite-Theory-and-the-2003-Iraq-Occupation-by-the-United-States-How-US-Corporate%2FNouri%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367706913%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerica%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98best%20and%20brightest%E2%80%99%20took%20the%20big%20decisions%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Iraq%20war%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20its%20subsequent%20occupation%2C%20civil%20war%2C%20and%20its%20current%20near-failed%20state%20condition.%20Therefore%2C%20given%20how%20thorough%2C%20astute%20and%20shrewd%20this%20group%20of%20US%20elites%20were%2C%20it%20is%20unconvincing%20to%20accept%20the%20security%20school%20argument%20that%20US%20foreign%20policy%20decision%20making%20could%20be%20reduced%20to%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS1045235409000197%2523preview-section-abstract%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccidents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FSquandered-Victory-Larry-Diamond%2Fdp%2F0805080082%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98mistakes%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20the%20result%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FIraq-Fragments-Occupation-Its-Legacy%2Fdp%2F0801444578%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98poor%20planning%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20elites%20who%20took%20key%20decisions%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FElite-Theory-and-the-2003-Iraq-Occupation-by-the-United-States-How-US-Corporate%2FNouri%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367706913%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIraq%20war%20and%20occupation%20were%20embedded%20in%20and%20driven%20by%20state-corporate%20interests%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20majority%20of%20the%20decision-makers%20%E2%80%93%20prior%20to%20their%20positions%20in%20the%20Bush%20elite%20%E2%80%93%20were%20major%20state-corporate%20players.%20Moreover%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Bush%20elite%20were%20connected%20to%20each%20other%20through%20numerous%20elite%20organisations%20and%20networks.%20Those%20elite%20networks%20facilitated%20the%20flows%20of%20ideas%20and%20people%20between%20the%20American%20state%20and%20the%20corporate%20community%20to%20such%20an%20important%20extent%20that%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20draw%20a%20line%20between%20them%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FThink-Tanks-Power-Foreign-Policy%2Fdp%2F1403921032%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etruly%20a%20state-private%20network%20of%20power%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20is%20in%20this%20rarefied%20and%20exclusive%20world%20of%20transnational%20corporations%2C%20with%20their%20funded%20elite%20think%20tanks%20and%20foundations%2C%20that%20the%20world-views%20of%20US%20state%20elites%20are%20shaped%20and%20crystallised.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20future%2C%20these%20exclusive%20networks%20enabled%20the%20widely-condemned%20ideas%20contained%20in%20a%20now-leaked%20document%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F1992%2F03%2F11%2Fkeeping-the-us-first%2F31a774aa-fcd9-45be-8526-ceafc933b938%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDefence%20Planning%20Guidance%201992%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20to%20morph%20into%20the%20blueprint%20of%C2%A0%20the%20neoconservative%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rrojasdatabank.info%2Fpfpc%2FPNAC---statement%252520of%252520principles.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProject%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Century%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20before%20evolving%20into%20the%20post-9-11%20consensus%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgeorgewbush-whitehouse.archives.gov%2Fnsc%2Fnss%2F2002%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhite%20House%E2%80%99s%20National%20Security%20Strategy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(NSS)%20of%202002.%20The%20NSS%20would%20cause%20its%20own%20mass%20destruction%20on%20a%20hoped-for%20road%20to%20unrivalled%20US%20military%20power%20and%20primacy%20through%20regime%20change%20in%20Iraq.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20one%20implausibly%20argues%20that%20the%20US%20had%20the%20right%20ideas%20for%20Iraq%20in%202003%2C%20its%20approach%20and%20the%20audacity%20of%20it%20%E2%80%93%20the%20heavy%20bombing%20campaign%2C%20marginalisation%20of%20Iraqis%2C%20the%20corruption%20by%20the%20occupation%20authorities%2C%20un-democratic%20co-optation%20of%20Iraqi%20elites%2C%20the%20violation%20of%20international%20law%2C%20zero-bid%20contracts%20to%20corporations%20where%20US%20decision-makers%20had%20interests%20(and%20to%20Bush%20election%20campaign%20donors)%20%E2%80%93%20alongside%20a%20clear%20disregard%20for%20the%20will%2C%20interests%20and%20security%20of%20ordinary%20Iraqis%2C%20contributed%20to%20a%20deadly%20anti-US%20insurgency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDestroy%20Iraq%20and%20let%20friends%20and%20loyalists%20rebuild%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EState-c%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eorporate%20elites%20making%20decisions%20in%20Iraq%20meant%20that%20the%20financial%20incentives%20of%20the%20war%20would%20be%20prioritised%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20bombing%20campaign.%20While%20in%20the%201991%20Gulf%20War%2C%20the%20US%20fired%20around%20300%20Tomahawk%20cruise%20missiles%20in%20a%20five-week%20period%2C%20in%202003%2C%20over%20380%20were%20launched%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eevery%20day%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20March%2020%2C%202003%20through%20to%20May%202%2C%20totalling%20over%2020%2C000%20missiles.%20This%20was%2070%25%20of%20the%20total%20stock%20of%20such%20missiles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20destruction%20comes%20re-building%2C%20and%20zero-bid%20contracts%20were%20handed%20out%20to%20American%20companies%20including%20in%20which%20Bush%20administration%20officials%20owned%20shares.%20The%20biggest%20recipient%20of%20contracts%20was%20Haliburton%2C%20which%20received%20%2439.5%20billion%2C%20and%20in%20which%20US%20Vice%20President%20Dick%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2Fcifamerica%2F2011%2Fjun%2F08%2Fdick-cheney-halliburton-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECheney%20had%20continued%20to%20hold%20shares%20despite%20being%20in%20public%20office%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Though%20the%20US%20was%20advertising%20its%20promise%20of%20freedom%20to%20Iraqis%20in%20pre-%20and%20wartime%20broadcasts%2C%20the%20real%20freedom%20was%20for%20US%20corporations%2C%20whose%20path%20to%20riches%20was%20paved%20by%20the%20Coalition%20Provisional%20Authority%20(CPA)%2C%20led%20by%20Paul%20Bremer%20(who%20had%20attended%20the%20same%20preparatory%20school%20as%20George%20W.%20Bush).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tampabay.com%2Farchive%2F2004%2F08%2F09%2Fbremer-s-100-orders-for-iraq-are-illegal%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBremer%2C%20a%20privatisation%20expert%2C%20imposed%20over%20100%20laws%20devised%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20to%20replace%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Baa%E2%80%99thist%20constitution%E2%80%99%20which%20historically%20prevented%20foreign%20ownership%20and%20was%20part%20of%20a%20system%20that%20placed%20tariffs%20on%20foreign%20imports.%20This%20meant%20contracts%20were%20awarded%20with%20little%20oversight%2C%20foreign%20firms%20operated%20without%20restraint%2C%20and%20a%20torrent%20of%20money%20flowed%20back%20to%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20no%20wonder%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FtUPn7%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Economist%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20a%20piece%20less%20than%20six%20months%20into%20the%20occupation%20with%20the%20title%20%E2%80%98Let%E2%80%99s%20all%20go%20to%20the%20yard%20sale%2C%20if%20it%20all%20works%20out%2C%20Iraq%20will%20be%20a%20capitalist%E2%80%99s%20dream%E2%80%99.%20Some%20of%20the%20highlights%20include%20Bechtel%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0whose%20board%20members%20had%20close%20ties%20to%20the%20Bush%20administration%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corpwatch.org%2Farticle%2Firaq-bechtel-ends-iraq-rebuilding-after-rough-3-years%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20received%20%C2%A32.3%20billion%20in%20contracts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20second%20largest%20after%20Haliburton%2C%20to%20rebuild%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure%2C%20especially%20its%20electricity%20supplies%20which%20had%20been%20destroyed%20by%20US%20bombing.%20The-then%20CEO%20of%20Bechtel%2C%20multi-billionaire%2C%20Riley%20Bechtel%2C%20was%20a%20member%20of%20Bush%E2%80%99s%20Export%20Council%20which%20advised%20on%20how%20to%20create%20overseas%20markets%20for%20US%20corporations.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20Bechtel%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Jack%20Sheehan%2C%20was%20simultaneously%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Defense%20Policy%20Board%2C%20a%20government%20group%20that%20advised%20the%20Pentagon%20on%20the%20Iraq%20War.%20Bechtel%E2%80%99s%20former%20CEO%2C%20George%20Shultz%2C%20also%20an%20informal%20advisor%20to%20President%20Bush%2C%20had%20penned%20op-eds%20to%20promote%20the%20war%20and%20then%20later%20to%20%E2%80%98rebuild%E2%80%99%20the%20nation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20element%20of%20the%20privatisation%20agenda%20was%20outsourced.%20A%20Netherlands-based%20offshoot%20of%20KPMG%2C%20BearingPoint%2C%20was%20tasked%20with%20creating%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20private%20market-based%20economy%2C%20for%20a%20fee%20of%20%24240%20million.%20BearingPoint%20employees%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fshock-and-oil-iraq-s-billions-amp-the-white-house-connection-431977.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econtributed%20%24117%2C000%20in%20donations%20for%20both%20the%202000%20and%202004%20Bush%20election%20campaigns%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CDemocracy-building%E2%80%9D%20was%20outsourced%20to%20the%20North%20Carolina-based%20Research%20Triangle%20Institute%20for%20the%20figure%20of%20%24466%20million.%20Its%20CEO%2C%20James%20Mayfield%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FShock-Doctrine-Rise-Disaster-Capitalism%2Fdp%2F0141024534%2Fref%3Dasc_df_0141024534%2F%3Ftag%3Dgoogshopuk-21%26linkCode%3Ddf0%26hvadid%3D310816411121%26hvpos%3D%26hvnetw%3Dg%26hvrand%3D15368938615135119332%26hvpone%3D%26hvptwo%3D%26hvqmt%3D%26hvdev%3Dc%26hvdvcmdl%3D%26hvlocint%3D%26hvlocphy%3D9046081%26hvtargid%3Dpla-457241838129%26psc%3D1%26th%3D1%26psc%3D1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpected%20Iraqis%20to%20erect%20a%20statue%20of%20him%20as%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98founder%20of%20democracy%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20100%20US%20laws%20imposed%20on%20Iraq%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20laws%20of%20military%20occupation%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Forder-17-a-free-pass-in-iraq%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECPA%20Order%2017%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20gave%20full%20impunity%20from%20prosecution%20to%20US%20contractors%20from%20both%20Iraqi%20and%20international%20law.%20Hence%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2006%2F03%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fus-contractor-found-guilty-of-3-million-fraud-in-iraq.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECuster%20Battles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fthe-dark-truth-about-blackwater%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBlackwater%20Security%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20got%20away%20with%20corruption%20and%20murderous%20war%20crimes%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20fact%20that%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20grid%20was%20left%20worse%20off%20after%20Bechtel%20failed%20to%20deliver%20on%20its%20contractual%20obligations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIt%20gets%20worse%3A%20US%20elites%20install%20corrupt%2C%20unrepresentative%20elites%2C%20call%20it%20democracy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20real%20problem%2C%20however%2C%20was%20bigger%20and%20more%20consequential%20than%20lucrative%20contracts.%20It%20was%20that%20having%20pillaged%20the%20land%2C%20US%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FElite-Theory-and-the-2003-Iraq-Occupation-by-the-United-States-How-US-Corporate%2FNouri%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9780367706913%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecorporate%20elites%20re-engineered%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20political%20system%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20US%20occupiers%20used%20divide-and-conquer%20strategies%20in%20the%20Iraqi%20constitution-making%20process%20in%20a%20country%20so%20intricately%20sensitive%20to%20division.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIraq%E2%80%99s%20future%20political%20system%20in%20practice%20would%20be%20decided%20by%20groups%20of%20Iraqi%20elites%20that%20the%20US%20has%20previously%20trained%20and%20supported%2C%20in%20a%20power-sharing%20settlement%20that%20was%20corrupt%20and%20anti-democratic%20to%20its%20core.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnrepresentative%20Iraqi%20political%20elites%20have%20since%20looted%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20resources%2C%20with%20millions%20of%20people%20bereft%20of%20prospects.%C2%A0As%20the%20majority%20of%20people%20have%20struggled%20with%20existential%20crises%2C%20Iraqi%20elites%20have%20continued%20to%20govern%20through%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2019%2F12%2F4%2Fmuhasasa-the-political-system-reviled-by-iraqi-protesters%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98muhasassa%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(the%20US-introduced%20quota-based%20political%20system)%20and%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Firaqs-discontent-its-roots-and-how-to-begin-fixing-it-124959%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98wasta%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(nepotism)%20systems.%20Despite%20divides%20along%20ethnic%20and%20sectarian%20lines%20creating%20disagreement%20between%20competing%20sects%2C%20there%20is%20an%20inter-elite%20unity%20that%20transcends%20these%20divisions%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20forming%20post-election%20political%20coalitions%20in%20government.%C2%A0Iraqi%20e%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Elections%20don%E2%80%99t%20decide%20political%20outcomes%3B%20they%20create%20the%20conditions%20for%20deal%20brokering%20and%20sharing%20of%20the%20spoils.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20political%20formations%2C%20aimed%20at%20creating%20a%20governing%20majority%20bloc%2C%20are%20centred%20on%20sharing%20out%20large-budget%20oil-funded%20ministries%2C%20which%20control%20various%20regional%20institutions.%20Consequently%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epost-election%20government%20formation%20is%20interminable%2C%20with%20the%20most%20recent%20election%20period%20being%20the%20longest%20in%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20beating%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Felection-2015-32612828%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E290-day%20record%20set%20in%202010%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20These%20institutions%20control%20a%20massive%20number%20of%20jobs%20in%20a%20system%20in%20which%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fat-iraqs-polls-voters-seek-patronage-and-jobs%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evoters%20vote%20for%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20control%20the%20ministries%20they%20are%20employed%20by%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20was%20therefore%20no%20surprise%20that%20in%20the%20last%20%E2%80%93%20October%202021%E2%80%93%20election%2C%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtoninstitute.org%2Fpolicy-analysis%2Freflections-iraqs-october-elections-good-bad-and-still-unknown%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enine%20million%20Iraqis%20who%20voted%20were%20almost%20equal%20to%20the%20number%20of%20people%20on%20the%20public%20sector%20payroll.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnderlining%20the%20anti-popular%20character%20of%20the%20Iraqi%20state%2C%20dominant%20political%20blocs%20are%20also%20connected%20to%20%E2%80%93%20and%20influenced%20by%20%E2%80%93%20foreign%20actors%2C%20constituting%20a%20revolving%20door%20for%20external%20influence%20into%20the%20Iraqi%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20many%20competing%20global%20and%20regional%20actors%20inside%20Iraq%20range%20from%20the%20US%20and%20Turkey%20to%20Iran%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhen%20ISIS%20rose%2C%20Iran%20came%20to%20the%20rescue%20%E2%80%93%20but%20at%20what%20price%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20Iraqi%20government%20so%20focused%20on%20sharing%20out%20ministries%20based%20on%20ethno-sectarian%20quotas%2C%20and%20channelling%20budgets%20for%20salaries%20to%20loyalists%2C%20meant%20that%20Iraq%20lacked%20a%20unifying%20national%20identity.%20This%20proved%20costly%20when%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20was%20challenged%20by%20ISIS%2C%20which%20used%20its%20barbaric%20and%20criminal%20ideologies%20to%20penetrate%20a%20weak%20and%20divided%20Iraqi%20state%20and%20army.%20Iraq%2C%20post-2005%2C%20was%20too%20divided%20to%20secure%20its%20own%20borders%20and%20national%20security%2C%20its%20army%20divided%20between%20different%20sects%20and%20political%20parties.%20Eventually%20and%20in%20desperation%2C%20Iraq%20reached%20out%20to%20Iran%20to%20provide%20assistance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20US%20failed%2C%20Iran%20emerged%20as%20a%20helpful%20yet%20opportunistic%20power%20in%20Iraq.%20Despite%20being%20under%20the%20historically%20heaviest%20set%20of%20US%20sanctions%2C%20Iran%20flew%20through%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20to%20promote%20its%20own%20foreign%20policy%2C%20whilst%20utilising%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20corrupt%20cash-based%20economy%20to%20fund%20its%20ventures.%20Enabling%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20Shiites%20in%20a%C2%A0Sunni-dominated%20Middle%20East%20remained%20ambitious%20yet%20achievable%2C%20with%20Iraq%20being%20the%20central%20pivot%20point%20economically%20and%20militarily.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETehran%E2%80%99s%20sophisticated%20approach%20means%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F07%2F15%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Firan-iraq-iranian-power.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20Iranian%20influence%20in%20Iraq%20is%20multi-faceted%2C%20embedded%20and%20effectively%20maintained%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20whereby%20the%20economic%20and%20security%20aims%20of%20Tehran%20are%20pursued%20through%20Baghdad.%20For%20example%2C%20Tehran%20plays%20an%20active%20role%20in%20influencing%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20cabinet%20members%20and%20other%20ministers%2C%20whilst%20also%20supporting%20(advising%2C%20funding%20and%20arming)%20political%20parties%20and%20individual%20candidates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIran%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20is%20all-encompassing%2C%20based%20on%20a%20willingness%20to%20work%20with%20all%20political%20parties%20inside%20Iraq%20in%20a%20tailored%2C%20interest-based%20and%20effective%20way%2C%20drawing%20on%20various%20commonalities.%20Naturally%20this%20enables%20influence%20in%20impacting%20national%20strategy%2C%20spreading%20ideologies%20and%20using%20leverage%20in%20other%20areas%20(especially%20militias)%20for%20political%20bargaining.%20Simultaneously%2C%20there%20are%20consistent%20%E2%80%93%20direct%20and%20indirect%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-cyber-iran-specialreport-idUSKCN1NZ1FT%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eattempts%20at%20embedding%20pro-Iranian%20sentiments%20and%20anti-US%20and%20anti-Saudi%20Arabia%20ideology%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20political%20parties%2C%20universities%2C%20religious%20venues%2C%20TV%2C%20radio%20and%20various%20other%20means.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20that%20Iraq%20has%20a%20massive%20internal%20consumer%20market%20of%20around%2040%20million%2C%20Iran%20dominates%20commercial%20activities.%20This%20ranges%20from%20food%2C%20construction%20materials%2C%20and%20pharmaceuticals%20through%20to%20services%3B%20from%20security%20to%20construction%20and%20even%20garbage%20removal%20services.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%2C%20well%20known%20Iranian%20state-sponsored%20and%20connected%20militias%20and%20proxies%20are%20embedded%20into%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20military%20and%20security%20services.%20The%20militias%20were%20made%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2016%2F11%2Firaq-parliament-passes-law-legalising-shia-militias-161126133010696.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20permanent%20fixture%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0in%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20security%20forces%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethanks%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIraqi%20parliament%20in%202016.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%202011%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usip.org%2Fpublications%2F2019%2F07%2Firaq-timeline-2003-war%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprotests%20and%20popular%20movements%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20challenged%20elite%20dominance%20or%20questioned%20the%20government%20%E2%80%93%20or%20their%20domination%20by%20Iran%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20violently%20repressed.%20The%20presence%20of%20Iran%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Iraqi%20politics%20has%20been%20fortified%20by%20a%20Shiite-dominated%20government%20that%20depends%20on%20the%20Iranian%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2019%2F07%2F31%2Firan-backed-militias-are-in-iraq-to-stay%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPopular%20Mobilisation%20Forces%20(PMF)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0to%20maintain%20order%20in%20Iraq%2C%20with%20many%20reports%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-iraq-protests-iran-snipers-exclusive%2Fexclusive-iran-backed-militias-deployed-snipers-in-iraq-protests-sources-idUSKBN1WW0B1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20use%20of%20snipers%20by%20Iranian-backed%20militias%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0in%20anti-government%20protests%20since%202019.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Geographically%2C%20Iranian-backed%20proxies%20hold%20key%20strategic%20roles%20and%20locations%20throughout%20Iraq%20which%20are%20often%20also%20used%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F03068374.2021.1912470%3FjournalCode%3Draaf20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eadvance%20other%20interests%20separate%20to%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20national%20and%20security%20aims%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(for%20example%20many%20militia%20groups%20carry%20their%20own%20flags%2C%20have%20their%20own%20ideologies%20and%20have%20been%20officially%20recorded%20in%20their%20targeting%20of%20Sunni%20and%20Kurdish%20groups%20indiscriminately%2C%20forcing%20many%20internal%20displacements).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20Obama%20administration%E2%80%99s%20attempts%20at%20keeping%20Iran%20in%20check%20through%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F23473538%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evigorous%20sanctions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20programme%20%E2%80%93%20labelled%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2012%2F01%2F23%2Fworld%2Fmeast%2Firan-sanctions-effects%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98the%20most%20extensive%20sanctions%20ever%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20President%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Mahmoud%20Ahmadinejad%20%E2%80%93%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20of%20overcoming%20economic%20restrictions%20depended%20on%20dominating%20Iraq.%20By%202017%2C%20all%20markets%20in%20Iraq%20were%20filled%20with%20Iranian%20produce%2C%20TV%20channels%20were%20dominated%20by%20pro-Iran%20broadcasts%2C%20illegal%20drugs%20were%20being%20shipped%20in%2C%20and%20even%20the%20bricks%20and%20cement%20for%20construction%20came%20from%20across%20the%20border.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F07%2F15%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Firan-iraq-iranian-power.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIraq%20literally%20depends%20on%20Iran%20for%20almost%20everything%20except%20oil%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20desperate%20US%20position%20in%20the%20Middle-East%20%E2%80%93%20as%20an%20immediate%20result%20of%20the%20illegal%20war%20%E2%80%93%20focused%20on%20countering%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20Iraq%20and%20the%20region.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202021%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-50324912%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIran%E2%80%99s%20presence%20in%20the%20region%20had%20expanded%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20beyond%20the%20strongholds%20of%20Iraq%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20and%20Palestine%2C%20and%20into%20Syria%20and%20Yemen%2C%20with%20activities%20and%20influence%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Bahrain%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Afghanistan%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fmaps%2Fembed%3Fpb%3D!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d13741552.774541881!2d33.09846607531098!3d32.76914978656449!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x1557823d54f54a11%253A0x6da561bba2061602!2sIraq!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1695107098669!5m2!1sen!2sin%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20quiet%20yet%20significant%20emergence%20in%20the%20region%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20distraction%20of%20Iran%20took%20the%20focus%20away%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20which%20capitalised%20on%20US%20failures%20in%20the%20Middle-East%20from%20as%20early%20as%202006.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmepc.org%2Fspeeches%2Farabs-take-chinese-wife-sino-arab-relations-decade-come%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20region%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20states%20viewed%20China%20as%20a%20trusted%20power%20that%20would%20do%20business%20with%20them%20without%20imposing%20ideologies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20whilst%20appreciating%20partnerships%20as%20opposed%20to%20insulting%20the%20region%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20values%20or%20traditions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20influence%20has%20redesigned%20the%20regional%20landscape%2C%20moving%20beyond%20energy%20and%20into%20deeper%20economic%2C%20geopolitical%20and%20strategic%20spheres.%20Because%20China%E2%80%99s%20approach%20is%20respectful%20and%20non-interventionist%2C%20deals%20with%20Beijing%20are%20welcome.%20As%20the%20US%20has%20openly%20shifted%20its%20strategic%20focus%20to%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20China%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20key%20Middle%20East%20player.%20Noteworthy%20trends%20include%20China%E2%80%99s%20regional%20economic%20activities%20with%20numerous%20memoranda%20of%20understanding%20as%20well%20as%20strategic%20partnerships%2C%20including%20with%20regional%20organisations%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fmenasource%2Fchina-is-getting-comfortable-with-the-gulf-cooperation-council-the-west-must-pragmatically-adapt-to-its-growing-regional-influence%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChina-Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(GCC)%20Strategic%20Dialogue%20of%202010.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202022%2C%20China%20held%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fchina-plans-summit-of-persian-gulf-arab-and-iranian-leaders-as-new-middle-east-role-takes-shape-357cfd7e%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20China-Arab%20States%20summit%20and%20its%20first%20China-GCC%20Summit%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20broadcasting%20its%20commitment%20to%20more%20strategic%20partnerships%20focused%20on%20diversifying%20economic%20development%20beyond%20oil.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Feconographics%2Fstrengthening-ties-china-and-the-gcc%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20even%20replaced%20the%20European%20Union%20as%20the%20GCC%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trading%20partner%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20through%20bilateral%20trade%2C%20whilst%20in%202023%2C%20it%20became%20the%20biggest%20non-trading%20partner%20of%20the%20UAE%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20this%20is%20without%20mentioning%20the%20ground-breaking%20influence%20of%20the%20famous%20%E2%80%98Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%E2%80%99%20(BRI)%20which%20is%20the%20centrepiece%20of%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20towards%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20its%20investments%20are%20targeted.%20Iraq%20has%20been%20a%20major%20beneficiary%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20investment%20through%20the%20BRI%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Firaq-was-top-target-chinas-belt-road-2021-study-2022-02-02%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereceiving%20%2410.5%20billion%20in%20construction%20contracts%20in%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20whilst%20the%20Autonomous%20Kurdistan%20Region%20of%20Iraq%20is%20set%20to%20receive%20%2410%20billion%20of%20infrastructure%20projects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20worrying%20for%20the%20US%20is%20the%20Iran-China%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F03%2F27%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fchina-iran-deal.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CComprehensive%20Strategic%20Partnership%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20agreement%2C%20with%2010%25%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20total%20BRI%20budget%20at%20a%20staggering%20%24400%20billion.%20It%20is%20no%20surprise%20that%20155%20countries%20are%20signed%20up%2C%20including%20the%20key%20regional%20players%20of%20Russia%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Egypt%2C%20UAE%20and%20Malaysia.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20long-term%20US%20ally%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20has%20secured%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20value%20BRI%20projects%20(worth%20%24195.7%20billion)%20with%20well%20over%20a%20hundred%20commissioned%20developments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20if%20one%20somehow%20down-plays%20China%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20economic%20and%20strategic%20role%20in%20the%20region%2C%20ignoring%20its%20diplomatic%20role%20is%20impossible.%20The%20way%20China%20presents%20itself%20as%20neutral%20and%20non-aligned%20has%20enabled%20it%20to%20promote%20peace%2C%20mediate%20where%20needed%20in%20the%20high-profile%20Syria%20and%20Yemen%20conflicts%2C%20and%20the%20peace%20negotiations%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20JCPOA%20process.%20However%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20and%20tangible%20example%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F04%2F06%2Firan-saudi-arabia-deal-agreement-china-meeting-beijing%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eimportant%20and%20influential%20role%20of%20China%20was%20the%20way%20it%20managed%20to%20bring%20Iran%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20together%20in%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20is%20even%20competing%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20weaponry%20after%20the%20US%20reduced%20advanced%20weapons%E2%80%99%20sales%20to%20the%20region.%20During%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20China%20took%20the%20opportunity%20to%20provide%20aid%20to%20states%20who%20needed%20it%2C%20as%20well%20as%20leading%20in%20providing%20solutions%20through%20lockdowns%20as%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20father%20of%20the%20liberal%20international%20order%20%E2%80%93%20started%20to%20attack%20its%20own%20ideas%20of%20internationalism%20through%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20nationalistic%20America%20First%20policies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EConclusion%3A%20What%20started%20in%20Iraq%20has%20spread%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20matter%20how%20much%20aid%20or%20weaponry%20the%20US%20provides%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20it%20cannot%20hide%20the%20fact%20that%20its%20own%20actions%20in%20Iraq%20(let%20alone%20NATO%20expansion)%20have%20intricately%20influenced%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20warfare%2C%20perhaps%20the%20biggest%20cost%20of%20the%20Iraq%20war%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scienceopen.com%2Fhosted-document%3Fdoi%3D10.13169%2Fjglobfaul.8.2.0186%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerica%20demonstrating%20that%20international%20laws%20have%20no%20power%20to%20regulate%20or%20deter%20illegal%20wars%20and%20occupations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20For%20Russia%2C%20the%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20in%202014%20was%20perhaps%20a%20testing%20of%20the%20waters%2C%20before%20its%20formal%20onslaught%20in%20invading%20Ukraine%20in%202022.%20One%20wonders%20if%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Ukraine%20would%20ever%20have%20happened%20had%20America%20acted%20more%20responsibly%20in%20Iraq%2C%20adhered%20to%20international%20laws%2C%20or%20at%20least%20had%20been%20held%20to%20account%20by%20them%2C%20instead%20of%20setting%20this%20precedent%20of%20destruction%20without%20accountability.%20The%20fact%20that%20they%20did%20not%20has%20caused%20many%20repercussions%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20which%20continue%20to%20weaken%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20global%20position%20and%20shore%20up%20a%20messy%20multipolar%20world%20order%20where%20domestic%20and%20international%20disorder%2C%20or%20at%20least%20radical%20change%2C%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJohn%20Quincy%20Adams%20claimed%20that%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%9Cgoes%20not%20abroad%2C%20in%20search%20of%20monsters%20to%20destroy%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%20He%20was%20wrong%20in%201821%20when%20those%20words%20were%20uttered%3B%20and%20those%20words%20are%20even%20more%20wrong%20now.%20It%20is%20more%20apt%20to%20quote%20the%20more%20accurate%20statement%20of%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr%2C%20in%201967%3A%20The%20United%20States%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgreatest%20purveyor%20of%20violence%20in%20the%20world%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20exporter%20of%20monstrous%20levels%20of%20bloodshed%2C%20the%20destroyer%20of%20independent%20states%20and%20of%20popular%20aspirations%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20global%20south.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20its%20illegal%20invasion%20and%20occupation%20of%20Iraq%2C%20the%20US%20got%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20it%20bargained%20for%2C%20and%20released%20forces%20of%20destruction%20and%20construction%20that%20signal%20the%20end%20of%20the%20American%20century.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDr%20Bamo%20Nouri%20is%20an%20award-winning%20lecturer%20in%20International%20Relations%20at%20the%20University%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWest%20London%2C%20an%20Honorary%20Research%20Fellow%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20and%20a%20One%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYoung%20World%20Ambassador.%20Born%20in%20Slemani%2C%20Iraq%2C%20he%20is%20also%20an%20independent%20investigative%20journalist%20and%20writer%20with%20interests%20in%20American%20foreign%20policy%20and%20the%20international%20and%20domestic%20politics%20of%20the%20Middle%20East.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EElite%20Theory%20and%20the%202003%20Iraq%20Occupation%20by%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a