div%3E%20%3Cp%3ETrudeau%20told%20parliament%20that%20he%20had%20already%20briefed%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20leaders%20about%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20these%20allegations%20are%20true%2C%20they%20represent%20an%20outrageous%20affront%20to%20Canada%2C%20to%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty.%20Our%20citizens%20must%20be%20safe%20from%20extrajudicial%20killings%20of%20all%20kinds%2C%20most%20of%20all%2C%20from%20foreign%20governments%2C%E2%80%9D%20Conservative%20leader%20Pierre%20Poilievre%20was%20quoted%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EGlobe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20saying.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CCanadians%20deserve%20to%20be%20protected%20on%20Canadian%20soil.%20We%20call%20on%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20act%20with%20utmost%20transparency%20as%20authorities%20investigate%20this%20murder%2C%20because%20the%20truth%20must%20come%20out.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CLet%20us%20lock%20arms%20and%20join%20hands%20in%20condemning%20this%20murder%2C%20standing%20with%20the%20family%20and%20the%20friends%20of%20this%20victim.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20put%20aside%20our%20difference%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20One%20law%20for%20all%20our%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Ftrudeau-indian-government-nijjar-1.6970498%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECBC%20reported%20him%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENew%20Democratic%20Party%20leader%20Jagmeet%20Singh%20reacted%20to%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20disclosure%20by%20saying%20the%20Modi%20government%C2%A0has%20pursued%20%E2%80%9Cdivision%2C%20violence%2C%20persecution%E2%80%9D%20and%20was%20%E2%80%9Cattacking%20those%20who%20are%20critical%E2%80%9D%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20public%20safety%20minister%20Dominic%20LeBlanc%20announced%20that%20David%20Vigneault%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Canadian%20Security%20Intelligence%20Service%2C%20and%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20adviser%2C%20Jody%20Thomas%2C%20had%20also%20recently%20visited%20India%20to%20discuss%20the%20assassination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20prime%20minister%20was%20in%20India%20for%20the%20G-20%20summit%2C%20during%20which%20he%20had%20short%20and%20tense%20meeting%20with%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20He%20was%20the%20only%20leader%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20attend%20the%20official%20banquet%20hosted%20by%20the%20Indian%20president%20on%20Saturday%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20meeting%20on%20Sunday%20(September%2010)%2C%20the%20Indian%20readout%20said%20that%20Modi%20raised%20%E2%80%9Cstrong%20concerns%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20activities%20of%20pro-Khalistan%20extremist%20groups.%20Trudeau%20told%20reporters%20that%20he%20had%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20interference%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20Indian%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20Indian%20ambassador%20to%20Canada%20had%20revealed%20that%20Ottawa%20had%20sought%20a%20pause%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctvnews.ca%2Fpolitics%2Findia-envoy-to-canada-says-ottawa-has-asked-to-take-a-pause-in-trade-talks-1.6544470%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewithin%20the%20last%20month%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20on%20negotiation%20for%20a%20free%20trade%20agreement%2C%20but%20had%20refused%20to%20give%20any%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20Canada%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctvnews.ca%2Fpolitics%2Fng-postpones-team-canada-trade-mission-to-india-amid-strained-relations-1.6562643%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epostponed%20a%20pre-scheduled%20trade%20mission%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20was%20to%20be%20led%20by%20Minister%20Mary%20Ng%20for%20five%20days%20from%20October%209%20in%20Mumbai.%20There%20was%20no%20official%20explanation%20given%20for%20the%20postponement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuoting%20a%20Canadian%20government%20source%2C%20CBC%20reports%20that%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20NSA%2C%20who%20was%20in%20Delhi%20for%20the%20G20%2C%20%E2%80%9Cquietly%E2%80%9D%20flew%20to%20London%20instead%20of%20Ottawa%20where%20she%20%E2%80%9Cinformed%20the%20UK%20government%20that%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20India%20were%20about%20to%20get%20worse%20now%20that%20Canada%20had%20credible%20evidence%20linking%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20the%20source%20said.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20summoned%20the%20Canadian%20high%20commissioner%20at%20least%20twice%20this%20year%20to%20protest%20the%20activities%20of%20Khalistan%20activists%20in%20Canada.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-envoy-summoned-breach%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20protested%20the%20%E2%80%9Cactions%20of%20separatist%20and%20extremist%20elements%20against%20our%20diplomatic%20Mission%20and%20Consulates%20in%20Canada%E2%80%9D%20after%20rallies%20organised%20by%20them.%20In%20July%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findiapro-khalistani-posters-canada%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20again%20summoned%20the%20Canadian%20high%20commissioner%20over%20the%20issue%20of%20pro-Khalistan%20posters%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20bearing%20photos%20of%20Indian%20diplomats%20%E2%80%93%20that%20accused%20the%20Indian%20government%20of%20being%20behind%20the%20killing%20of%20H%20Nijjar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20is%20a%20developing%20story%20and%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20more%20details%20become%20available%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695075357000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fup